# Known, accepted, remediated-in-tree residual risk — not a live leak.
#
# Incident: commit f8eaec7 (2026-07-18, "Prepare release 1.9.1 with
# security framework, pilot/review docs, and improved README") added
# docs/governance/REVIEW.md containing a local-machine email on a
# .local mDNS hostname, and an absolute file:// path revealing a local
# username — see PR #28's description for the exact original strings.
#
# Remediation: fixed going forward in PR #28 ("Scrub personal info from
# the governance review checklist"), which replaced all three with
# generic placeholders. Git history was deliberately left unrewritten —
# a force-push rewrite would break every existing clone/fork over a
# non-secret, low-severity leak — so these exact historical fingerprints
# are allowlisted here instead, scoped to commit+file+rule+line. Any
# *new* finding, including a new occurrence of the same pattern in a
# different commit or file, is not covered by this ignore and still
# fails the build.
#
# f8eaec7:docs/governance/REVIEW.md:15 — file:// path leaking username
f8eaec7d26a1ff710b6aecc91cf912d9549f653c:docs/governance/REVIEW.md:privacy-local-file-uri:15
# f8eaec7:docs/governance/REVIEW.md:15 — /Users/<name> path, same line
f8eaec7d26a1ff710b6aecc91cf912d9549f653c:docs/governance/REVIEW.md:privacy-macos-user-path:15
# f8eaec7:docs/governance/REVIEW.md:10 — .local-hostname email address
f8eaec7d26a1ff710b6aecc91cf912d9549f653c:docs/governance/REVIEW.md:privacy-local-hostname-email:10
